quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  55,26,All who are on it will perish
  55,27,"and there will remain the Face (Person) of your Fosterer, Possessor of glory and honour"
  55,28,So which of the bounties of your Fosterer will you both deny
  55,29,"Whoever is in the skies and the earth asks from Him, everyday (each moment) He is in a state (of intending something or implementing some affair)"
  55,30,So which of the bounties of your Fosterer will you both deny
  55,31,"We will free (Ourselves) for you, O you two weighty (things)"
  55,32,So which of the bounties of your Fosterer will you both deny
  55,33,"O assembly of jinn and mankind! if you are able to pass through the boundaries (or spheres) of the skies and the earth, then pass through, you will not pass through except with authority"
  55,34,So which of the bounties of your Fosterer will you both deny
  55,35,"Flames of fire (without smoke) and hot smoke (without flames) will be sent on you both, then you will not be able to defend"
  55,36,So which of the bounties of your Fosterer will you both deny
  55,37,So when the sky splits and becomes red like red hide
  55,38,So which of the bounties of your Fosterer will you both deny
  55,39,So on that day neither man nor jinn will be questioned about his sin
  55,40,So which of the bounties of your Fosterer will you both deny
  55,41,"The criminals will be recognised by their marks, so they will be caught by the forelocks and feet"
  55,42,So which of the bounties of your Fosterer will you both deny
  55,43,This is hell which the criminals denied
  55,44,they will go round between it and between hot boiling water
  55,45,So which of the bounties of your Fosterer will you both deny